      <h3>From Chemist To Programmer</h3>
        <p>Now, I have been a rubyist for nearly 3 years. I like writing codes. Maybe I will continue coding until someday we no more need this job.</p>
        <p>I majored applied chemistry in university. I like chemistry, yes, at least in middle school. But the regime and teaching style of university made me lose interests of chemistry.</p>
        <p>During my second year of university, I learnt VB Programming, which opened a door to the world of codes for me.</p>
        <p>I try to organize the steps how human solve the problems and to tell the computers by writing codes. I can't be more excited when I saw the right result jumping out of the screen.</p>
    </div>
